Chima Azubuike, Gombe Gombe State Government has proposed the sum of N130.5bn for the 2020 fiscal year. The budget tagged, ‘Budget of Change’, has N71bn for capital expenditure and N55bn for recurrent expenditure. The proposal will soon be transmitted to the state House of Assembly. The state Commissioner for Finance, Gambo Magaji, briefed journalists on Wednesday on the budget with the Permanent Secretary, Budget and Planning, Jalo Ali, immediately after the maiden meeting of the cabinet at the Government House, Gombe. Magaji said the state was expecting N49bn from federal allocation, and N11.11bn from Internally Generated Revenue. In the proposed budget, education, health and infrastructure were given priority. The commissioner disclosed that the budget would be funded through the federal allocation accruing to the state, internal borrowing and the IGR. The state government had on Tuesday organised a town hall meeting for stakeholders in the state to make input into the proposed budget. Copyright PUNCH.
